HTTP is stateless - it doesn't save data between requests.
Still, this functionality may come in handy (shopping basket on eshop, authorization, etc).
! For each user this data should be stored on server. This set of data is called session.

But there are more than one user. How to identify session of any client?
* With a use of cookies - information that is located on clients browser which is sent every request.

How session work?
* Client gets from server "JSESSIONID" cookie - unique user id
* With unique user id server identifies user and its session
! If browser cookies are deleted then server won't recognize user and its session